50tensorflow::DataType GetTensorFlowDataType(ArrayDataType data_type) {
51 switch (data_type) {
52 case ArrayDataType::kBool:
53 return tensorflow::DT_BOOL;
54 case ArrayDataType::kFloat:
55 return tensorflow::DT_FLOAT;
56 case ArrayDataType::kUint8:
57 return tensorflow::DT_UINT8;
58 case ArrayDataType::kInt32:
59 return tensorflow::DT_INT32;
60 case ArrayDataType::kInt64:
61 return tensorflow::DT_INT64;
62 case ArrayDataType::kString:
63 return tensorflow::DT_STRING;
64 default:
65 case ArrayDataType::kNone:
66 LOG(FATAL) << "Unsupported data type: " << static_cast<int>(data_type);
67 return tensorflow::DT_INVALID;
68 }
69}
70
71tensorflow::DataType GetTensorFlowDataType(const Model& model,
72 const string& array_name) {
73 return GetTensorFlowDataType(model.GetArray(array_name).data_type);
74}
75
76// TensorFlow sometimes forbids what it calls "legacy scalars",
77// which are 1-D shapes where the unique shape size is 1.
78// See OpKernel::IsLegacyScalar and OpKernel::allow_legacy_scalars.
79// For that reason, we generally avoid creating legacy scalars,
80// by detecting the case where a 1-D shape would be of size 1 and
81// replacing that by a 0-D shape.
82// However, there is a special circumstance where we must not do that
83// and must unconditionally create a 1-D shape even if it is going to
84// be of size 1: that is the case of bias vectors, with BiasAdd nodes.
85// Indeed, TensorFlow requires bias vectors to be 1-D; in the case of
86// a depth of 1, that would be a legacy scalar, so in that case we
87// must go ahead and keep the shape 1-D, letting it be a legacy scalar.
88enum class LegacyScalarPolicy { kAvoidLegacyScalars, kDoCreateLegacyScalars };
89
90void ExportFloatArray(const Shape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
91 TensorProto* output_tensor,
92 LegacyScalarPolicy legacy_scalar_policy) {
93 output_tensor->set_dtype(DT_FLOAT);
94 const int input_flat_size = RequiredBufferSizeForShape(input_shape);
95 auto* shape = output_tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
96
97 const int kDims = input_shape.dimensions_count();
98 if (legacy_scalar_policy == LegacyScalarPolicy::kDoCreateLegacyScalars ||
99 kDims > 1 || (kDims == 1 && input_shape.dims(0) > 1)) {
100 for (int i = 0; i < kDims; ++i) {
101 shape->add_dim()->set_size(input_shape.dims(i));
102 }
103 }
104 output_tensor->set_tensor_content(
105 string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(input_data),
106 sizeof(*input_data) * input_flat_size));
107}
108
109void ExportFloatArray(AxesOrder input_axes_order, const Shape& input_shape,
110 const float* input_data, AxesOrder output_axes_order,
111 TensorProto* output_tensor,
112 LegacyScalarPolicy legacy_scalar_policy) {
113 CHECK_EQ(AxesCount(output_axes_order), AxesCount(input_axes_order));
114 output_tensor->set_dtype(DT_FLOAT);
115 CHECK_EQ(input_shape.dimensions_count(), AxesCount(input_axes_order));
116 const int input_flat_size = RequiredBufferSizeForShape(input_shape);
117
118 Shape shuffled_shape;
119 ShuffleDims(input_shape, input_axes_order, output_axes_order,
120 &shuffled_shape);
121 std::vector<float> shuffled_data(input_flat_size);
122 ShuffleArray(input_shape, input_axes_order, output_axes_order, shuffled_shape,
123 input_data, shuffled_data.data());
124
125 ExportFloatArray(shuffled_shape, shuffled_data.data(), output_tensor,
126 legacy_scalar_policy);
127}
128
129bool HasAlreadyExportedConst(const string& name,
130 const GraphDef& tensorflow_graph) {
131 for (const auto& node : tensorflow_graph.node()) {
132 if (node.op() == "Const" && node.name() == name) {
133 return true;
134 }
135 }
136 return false;
137}
138
139void ConvertFloatTensorConst(const string& name, const Shape& input_shape,
140 const float* input_data,
141 AxesOrder input_axes_order,
142 AxesOrder output_axes_order,
143 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph,
144 LegacyScalarPolicy legacy_scalar_policy) {
145 if (HasAlreadyExportedConst(name, *tensorflow_graph)) {
146 return;
147 }
148 auto* const_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
149 const_op->set_op("Const");
150 const_op->set_name(name);
151 (*const_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
152 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
153 ExportFloatArray(input_axes_order, input_shape, input_data, output_axes_order,
154 tensor, legacy_scalar_policy);
155}

169 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();

174void ConvertFloatTensorConst(const Model& model, const string& name,
175 AxesOrder input_axes_order,
176 AxesOrder output_axes_order,
177 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
178 if (HasAlreadyExportedConst(name, *tensorflow_graph)) {
179 return;
180 }
181 auto* const_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
182 const_op->set_op("Const");
183 const_op->set_name(name);
184 (*const_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
185 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
186 CHECK(model.HasArray(name));
187 const auto& input_array = model.GetArray(name);
188 const auto& input_shape = input_array.shape();
189 CHECK(input_array.buffer);
190 CHECK(input_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
191 const float* input_data =
192 input_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
193 ExportFloatArray(input_axes_order, input_shape, input_data, output_axes_order,
194 tensor, LegacyScalarPolicy::kAvoidLegacyScalars);
195}

218void ConvertIntTensorConst(const Model& model, const string& name,
219 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
220 if (HasAlreadyExportedConst(name, *tensorflow_graph)) {
221 return;
222 }
223 CHECK(model.HasArray(name));
224 const auto& array = model.GetArray(name);
225 auto* const_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
226 const_op->set_op("Const");
227 const_op->set_name(name);
228 (*const_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
229 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
230 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
231 const auto& data = array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kInt32>().data;
232 for (auto index : data) {
233 tensor->add_int_val(index);
234 }
235 const auto& array_shape = array.shape();
236 auto* shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
237 for (int i = 0; i < array_shape.dimensions_count(); i++) {
238 shape->add_dim()->set_size(array_shape.dims(i));
239 }
240}

242void CreateIntTensorConst(const string& name, const std::vector<int32>& data,
243 const std::vector<int32>& shape,
244 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
245 if (HasAlreadyExportedConst(name, *tensorflow_graph)) {
246 return;
247 }
248 auto* const_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
249 const_op->set_op("Const");
250 const_op->set_name(name);
251 (*const_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
252 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
253 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
254 for (auto index : data) {
255 tensor->add_int_val(index);
256 }
257 auto* tensor_shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
258 int num_elements = 1;
259 for (int size : shape) {
260 tensor_shape->add_dim()->set_size(size);
261 num_elements *= size;
262 }
263 CHECK_EQ(num_elements, data.size());
264}

266void CreateMatrixShapeTensorConst(const string& name, int rows, int cols,
267 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
268 if (HasAlreadyExportedConst(name, *tensorflow_graph)) {
269 return;
270 }
271 auto* const_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
272 const_op->set_op("Const");
273 const_op->set_name(name);
274 (*const_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
275 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
276 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
277 const int32 data[2] = {cols, rows};
278 tensor->set_tensor_content(
279 string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(data), sizeof(data)));
280 auto* shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
281 shape->add_dim()->set_size(2);
282}

298void CreateReshapeShapeTensorConst(const string& name,
299 const std::vector<int32>& shape,
300 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
301 if (HasAlreadyExportedConst(name, *tensorflow_graph)) {
302 return;
303 }
304 auto* const_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
305 const_op->set_op("Const");
306 const_op->set_name(name);
307 (*const_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
308 auto* tensor = (*const_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
309 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
310 for (auto s : shape) {
311 tensor->add_int_val(s);
312 }
313 // TensorFlow sometimes forbids what it calls "legacy scalars",
314 // which are shapes of size 1 where the unique shape size is 1.
315 // See OpKernel::IsLegacyScalar and OpKernel::allow_legacy_scalars.
316 if (shape.size() > 1) {
317 auto* tensor_shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
318 tensor_shape->add_dim()->set_size(shape.size());
319 }
320}
321
322string WalkUpToConstantArray(const Model& model, const string& name) {
323 const Array& original_array = model.GetArray(name);
324 if (original_array.buffer) {
325 return name;
326 }
327 const auto* op = GetOpWithOutput(model, name);
328 CHECK(op);
329 CHECK(op->type == OperatorType::kFakeQuant);
330 const string& input_of_fakequant_name = op->inputs[0];
331 const Array& input_of_fakequant = model.GetArray(input_of_fakequant_name);
332 CHECK(input_of_fakequant.buffer);
333 return input_of_fakequant_name;
334}
335
336void ConvertConvOperator(const Model& model, const ConvOperator& src_op,
337 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
338 const bool has_bias = src_op.inputs.size() >= 3;
339 string conv_output = src_op.outputs[0];
340 if (has_bias) {
341 conv_output += "/conv";
342 }
343
344 auto* conv2d_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
345 conv2d_op->set_op("Conv2D");
346 conv2d_op->set_name(conv_output);
347 *conv2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
348 *conv2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
349 (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
350 const string& weights_array_name =
351 WalkUpToConstantArray(model, src_op.inputs[1]);
352 const auto& weights_array = model.GetArray(weights_array_name);
353 CHECK(weights_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
354 ConvertFloatTensorConst(model, weights_array_name, AxesOrder::kOHWI,
355 AxesOrder::kHWIO, tensorflow_graph);
356 auto& strides = (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["strides"];
357 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
358 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_height);
359 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_width);
360 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
361 if ((src_op.dilation_width_factor != 1) ||
362 (src_op.dilation_height_factor != 1)) {
363 auto& dilations = (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["dilations"];
364 dilations.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
365 dilations.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.dilation_height_factor);
366 dilations.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.dilation_width_factor);
367 dilations.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
368 }
369 string padding;
370 if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kSame) {
371 padding = "SAME";
372 } else if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kValid) {
373 padding = "VALID";
374 } else {
375 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
376 }
377 (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["padding"].set_s(padding);
378
379 if (has_bias) {
380 auto* biasadd_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
381 biasadd_op->set_op("BiasAdd");
382 biasadd_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
383 biasadd_op->add_input(conv_output);
384 biasadd_op->add_input(src_op.inputs[2]);
385 (*biasadd_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
386 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[2]));
387 const string& bias_array_name =
388 WalkUpToConstantArray(model, src_op.inputs[2]);
389 const auto& bias_array = model.GetArray(bias_array_name);
390 // TODO(b/62904716) Bias arrays should be 1-D, and used directly.
391 Shape bias_shape_1d = bias_array.shape();
392 UnextendShape(&bias_shape_1d, 1);
393 CHECK(bias_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
394 const float* bias_data =
395 bias_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
396 ConvertFloatTensorConst(bias_array_name, bias_shape_1d, bias_data,
397 AxesOrder::kOneAxis, AxesOrder::kOneAxis,
398 tensorflow_graph,
399 LegacyScalarPolicy::kDoCreateLegacyScalars);
400 }
401}
402
403void ConvertDepthwiseConvOperator(const Model& model,
404 const DepthwiseConvOperator& src_op,
405 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
406 const bool has_bias = src_op.inputs.size() >= 3;
407 string conv_output = src_op.outputs[0];
408 if (has_bias) {
409 conv_output += "/conv";
410 }
411
412 auto* dc2d_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
413 dc2d_op->set_op("DepthwiseConv2dNative");
414 dc2d_op->set_name(conv_output);
415 *dc2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
416 *dc2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
417 (*dc2d_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
418
419 // Our internal DepthwiseConv weights are 1 x H x W x OutputDepth.
420 // We need to convert that to H x W x InputDepth x Multiplier.
421 // That's only a matter of constructing a Dims object; the actual
422 // array layout is the same.
423 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[1]));
424 const string& src_weights_name =
425 WalkUpToConstantArray(model, src_op.inputs[1]);
426 const auto& src_weights_array = model.GetArray(src_weights_name);
427 const auto& src_weights_shape = src_weights_array.shape();
428 CHECK_EQ(src_weights_shape.dimensions_count(), 4);
429 const Shape dst_weights_shape =
430 Shape({src_weights_shape.dims(1), src_weights_shape.dims(2),
431 src_weights_shape.dims(3) / src_op.depth_multiplier,
432 src_op.depth_multiplier});
433 CHECK_EQ(src_weights_shape.dims(3) % src_op.depth_multiplier, 0);
434 CHECK(dst_weights_shape.dims(2) * dst_weights_shape.dims(3) ==
435 src_weights_shape.dims(3));
436 CHECK_EQ(src_weights_shape.dims(0), 1);
437
438 CHECK(src_weights_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
439 const float* src_weights_data =
440 src_weights_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
441 ConvertFloatTensorConst(src_weights_name, dst_weights_shape, src_weights_data,
442 AxesOrder::kHWIM, AxesOrder::kHWIM, tensorflow_graph);
443
444 auto& strides = (*dc2d_op->mutable_attr())["strides"];
445 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
446 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_height);
447 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_width);
448 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
449 string padding;
450 if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kSame) {
451 padding = "SAME";
452 } else if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kValid) {
453 padding = "VALID";
454 } else {
455 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
456 }
457 (*dc2d_op->mutable_attr())["padding"].set_s(padding);
458
459 if (has_bias) {
460 auto* biasadd_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
461 biasadd_op->set_op("BiasAdd");
462 biasadd_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
463 biasadd_op->add_input(conv_output);
464 biasadd_op->add_input(src_op.inputs[2]);
465 (*biasadd_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
466 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[2]));
467 const string& bias_name = WalkUpToConstantArray(model, src_op.inputs[2]);
468 const auto& bias_array = model.GetArray(bias_name);
469 // TODO(b/62904716) Bias arrays should be 1-D, and used directly.
470 Shape bias_shape_1d = bias_array.shape();
471 UnextendShape(&bias_shape_1d, 1);
472 CHECK(bias_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
473 const float* bias_data =
474 bias_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
475 ConvertFloatTensorConst(bias_name, bias_shape_1d, bias_data,
476 AxesOrder::kOneAxis, AxesOrder::kOneAxis,
477 tensorflow_graph,
478 LegacyScalarPolicy::kDoCreateLegacyScalars);
479 }
480}

482void ConvertTransposeConvOperator(const Model& model,
483 const TransposeConvOperator& src_op,
484 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
485 auto* conv2d_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
486 conv2d_op->set_op("Conv2DBackpropInput");
487 conv2d_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
488 *conv2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
489 *conv2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
490 *conv2d_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[2];
491 (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
492 const string& weights_array_name = WalkUpToConstantArray(
493 model, src_op.inputs[TransposeConvOperator::WEIGHTS]);
494 const auto& weights_array = model.GetArray(weights_array_name);
495 CHECK(weights_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
496 ConvertFloatTensorConst(model, weights_array_name, AxesOrder::kOHWI,
497 AxesOrder::kHWIO, tensorflow_graph);
498 auto& strides = (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["strides"];
499 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
500 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_height);
501 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_width);
502 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
503 string padding;
504 if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kSame) {
505 padding = "SAME";
506 } else if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kValid) {
507 padding = "VALID";
508 } else {
509 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
510 }
511 (*conv2d_op->mutable_attr())["padding"].set_s(padding);
512}

521 (*op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);

523}

536void ConvertFullyConnectedOperator(const Model& model,
537 const FullyConnectedOperator& src_op,
538 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
539 // Reshape input activations to have the shape expected by the MatMul.
540 const string reshape_output =
541 AvailableArrayName(model, src_op.outputs[0] + "/reshape");
542 const string reshape_shape =
543 AvailableArrayName(model, reshape_output + "/shape");
544 const auto& fc_weights_array = model.GetArray(src_op.inputs[1]);
545 const auto& fc_weights_shape = fc_weights_array.shape();
546 CHECK_EQ(fc_weights_shape.dimensions_count(), 2);
547 CreateMatrixShapeTensorConst(reshape_shape, fc_weights_shape.dims(1), -1,
548 tensorflow_graph);
549 auto* reshape_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
550 reshape_op->set_op("Reshape");
551 reshape_op->set_name(reshape_output);
552 reshape_op->add_input(src_op.inputs[0]);
553 reshape_op->add_input(reshape_shape);
554 (*reshape_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(
555 GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]));
556
557 const bool has_bias = src_op.inputs.size() >= 3;
558 string matmul_output = src_op.outputs[0];
559 if (has_bias) {
560 matmul_output += "/matmul";
561 }
562
563 // Transpose the RHS input from column-major to row-major to match TensorFlow
564 // expectations. This is the inverse of the transpose we do during
565 // ResolveTensorFlowMatMul.
566 const string transpose_output =
567 AvailableArrayName(model, matmul_output + "/transpose_weights");
568 const string transpose_perm =
569 AvailableArrayName(model, transpose_output + "/perm");
570 CreateIntTensorConst(transpose_perm, {1, 0}, {2}, tensorflow_graph);
571 auto transpose_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
572 transpose_op->set_op("Transpose");
573 transpose_op->set_name(transpose_output);
574 *transpose_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
575 *transpose_op->add_input() = transpose_perm;
576 (*transpose_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(
577 GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[1]));
578 (*transpose_op->mutable_attr())["Tperm"].set_type(DT_INT32);
579
580 auto* matmul_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
581 matmul_op->set_op("MatMul");
582 matmul_op->set_name(matmul_output);
583 *matmul_op->add_input() = reshape_output;
584 *matmul_op->add_input() = transpose_op->name();
585 (*matmul_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(
586 GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]));
587 (*matmul_op->mutable_attr())["transpose_a"].set_b(false);
588 (*matmul_op->mutable_attr())["transpose_b"].set_b(false);
589 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[1]));
590
591 // Add the bias, if it exists.
592 if (has_bias) {
593 auto* biasadd_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
594 biasadd_op->set_op("BiasAdd");
595 biasadd_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
596 biasadd_op->add_input(matmul_output);
597 biasadd_op->add_input(src_op.inputs[2]);
598 (*biasadd_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(
599 GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]));
600 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[2]));
601 const auto& bias_array = model.GetArray(src_op.inputs[2]);
602 // TODO(b/62904716) Bias arrays should be 1-D, and used directly.
603 Shape bias_shape_1d = bias_array.shape();
604 UnextendShape(&bias_shape_1d, 1);
605 CHECK(bias_array.buffer);
606 CHECK(bias_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
607 const float* bias_data =
608 bias_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
609 ConvertFloatTensorConst(WalkUpToConstantArray(model, src_op.inputs[2]),
610 bias_shape_1d, bias_data, AxesOrder::kOneAxis,
611 AxesOrder::kOneAxis, tensorflow_graph,
612 LegacyScalarPolicy::kDoCreateLegacyScalars);
613 }
614}

685 max_op->set_name(max_output);

734void ConvertSoftmaxOperator(const Model& model, const SoftmaxOperator& src_op,
735 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
736 string softmax_input;
737 Operator* providing_op = GetOpWithOutput(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
738 if (providing_op != nullptr &&
739 providing_op->type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowReshape) {
740 softmax_input = src_op.inputs[0];
741 } else {
742 // Insert a reshape operator that reduces the dimensions down to the 2 that
743 // are required for TensorFlow Logits.
744 const string reshape_output = src_op.outputs[0] + "/softmax_insert_reshape";
745 const string softmax_size = src_op.outputs[0] + "/softmax_insert_size";
746 softmax_input = reshape_output;
747
748 auto* reshape_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
749 reshape_op->set_op("Reshape");
750 reshape_op->set_name(reshape_output);
751 *reshape_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
752 *reshape_op->add_input() = softmax_size;
753 (*reshape_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
754
755 const auto& input_shape = model.GetArray(src_op.inputs[0]).shape();
756 int32 flattened_size = 1;
757 for (int i = 0; i < input_shape.dimensions_count() - 1; ++i) {
758 flattened_size *= input_shape.dims(i);
759 }
760 const std::vector<int32> shape_data = {
761 flattened_size, input_shape.dims(input_shape.dimensions_count() - 1)};
762 CreateReshapeShapeTensorConst(softmax_size, shape_data, tensorflow_graph);
763 }
764
765 auto* softmax_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
766 softmax_op->set_op("Softmax");
767 softmax_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
768 *softmax_op->add_input() = softmax_input;
769 // TensorFlow's Softmax doesn't seem to admit a 'beta' parameter
770 CHECK_EQ(src_op.beta, 1.f);
771 (*softmax_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
772}
773
774void ConvertLogSoftmaxOperator(const Model& model,
775 const LogSoftmaxOperator& src_op,
776 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
777 string softmax_input;
778 Operator* providing_op = GetOpWithOutput(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
779 if (providing_op != nullptr &&
780 providing_op->type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowReshape) {
781 softmax_input = src_op.inputs[0];
782 } else {
783 // Insert a reshape operator that reduces the dimensions down to the 2 that
784 // are required for TensorFlow Logits.
785 const string reshape_output =
786 src_op.outputs[0] + "/log_softmax_insert_reshape";
787 const string softmax_size = src_op.outputs[0] + "/log_softmax_insert_size";
788 softmax_input = reshape_output;
789
790 auto* reshape_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
791 reshape_op->set_op("Reshape");
792 reshape_op->set_name(reshape_output);
793 *reshape_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
794 *reshape_op->add_input() = softmax_size;
795 (*reshape_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
796
797 const auto& input_shape = model.GetArray(src_op.inputs[0]).shape();
798 int32 flattened_size = 1;
799 for (int i = 0; i < input_shape.dimensions_count() - 1; ++i) {
800 flattened_size *= input_shape.dims(i);
801 }
802 const std::vector<int32> shape_data = {
803 flattened_size, input_shape.dims(input_shape.dimensions_count() - 1)};
804 CreateReshapeShapeTensorConst(softmax_size, shape_data, tensorflow_graph);
805 }
806
807 auto* log_softmax_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
808 log_softmax_op->set_op("LogSoftmax");
809 log_softmax_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
810 *log_softmax_op->add_input() = softmax_input;
811 (*log_softmax_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
812}

814void ConvertL2NormalizationOperator(const L2NormalizationOperator& src_op,
815 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
816 const string square_output = src_op.outputs[0] + "/square";
817 const string sum_reduction_indices = src_op.outputs[0] + "/reduction_indices";
818 const string sum_output = src_op.outputs[0] + "/sum";
819 const string rsqrt_output = src_op.outputs[0] + "/rsqrt";
820 const string rsqrt_tiled_output = src_op.outputs[0] + "/rsqrt_tiled";
821
822 auto* sum_reduction_indices_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
823 sum_reduction_indices_op->set_op("Const");
824 sum_reduction_indices_op->set_name(sum_reduction_indices);
825 (*sum_reduction_indices_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
826 auto* sum_reduction_indices_tensor =
827 (*sum_reduction_indices_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
828 sum_reduction_indices_tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
829 auto* sum_reduction_indices_shape =
830 sum_reduction_indices_tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
831 auto* sum_reduction_indices_dim = sum_reduction_indices_shape->add_dim();
832 sum_reduction_indices_dim->set_size(2);
833 sum_reduction_indices_tensor->add_int_val(0);
834 sum_reduction_indices_tensor->add_int_val(1);
835
836 auto* square_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
837 square_op->set_op("Square");
838 square_op->set_name(square_output);
839 *square_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
840 (*square_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
841
842 auto* sum_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
843 sum_op->set_op("Sum");
844 sum_op->set_name(sum_output);
845 *sum_op->add_input() = square_output;
846 *sum_op->add_input() = sum_reduction_indices;
847 (*sum_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
848
849 auto* rsqrt_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
850 rsqrt_op->set_op("Rsqrt");
851 rsqrt_op->set_name(rsqrt_output);
852 *rsqrt_op->add_input() = sum_output;
853 (*rsqrt_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
854
855 auto* mul_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
856 mul_op->set_op("Mul");
857 mul_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
858 *mul_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
859 *mul_op->add_input() = rsqrt_output;
860 (*mul_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
861}

888void ConvertMaxPoolOperator(const MaxPoolOperator& src_op,
889 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
890 auto* maxpool_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
891 maxpool_op->set_op("MaxPool");
892 maxpool_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
893 *maxpool_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
894 auto& strides = (*maxpool_op->mutable_attr())["strides"];
895 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
896 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_height);
897 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_width);
898 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
899 string padding;
900 if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kSame) {
901 padding = "SAME";
902 } else if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kValid) {
903 padding = "VALID";
904 } else {
905 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
906 }
907 (*maxpool_op->mutable_attr())["padding"].set_s(padding);
908 (*maxpool_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
909 auto& ksize = (*maxpool_op->mutable_attr())["ksize"];
910 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
911 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.kheight);
912 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.kwidth);
913 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
914}

982void ConvertL2PoolOperator(const L2PoolOperator& src_op,
983 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {

985 const string avgpool_output = src_op.outputs[0] + "/avgpool";
986

989 square_op->set_name(square_output);
990 *square_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];

995 padding = "SAME";
996 } else if (src_op.padding.type == PaddingType::kValid) {
997 padding = "VALID";
998 } else {
999 LOG(FATAL) << "Bad padding (only SAME and VALID are supported)";
1000 }
1001
1002 auto* avgpool_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1003 avgpool_op->set_op("AvgPool");
1004 avgpool_op->set_name(avgpool_output);
1005 *avgpool_op->add_input() = square_output;

1007 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
1008 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_height);
1009 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.stride_width);
1010 strides.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
1011
1012 (*avgpool_op->mutable_attr())["padding"].set_s(padding);
1013 (*avgpool_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1014 auto& ksize = (*avgpool_op->mutable_attr())["ksize"];

1016 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.kheight);
1017 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(src_op.kwidth);
1018 ksize.mutable_list()->add_i(1);
1019
1020 auto* sqrt_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1021 sqrt_op->set_op("Sqrt");
1022 sqrt_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
1023 *sqrt_op->add_input() = avgpool_output;

1041 sqrt_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
1042 CHECK_EQ(src_op.inputs.size(), 1);
1043 *sqrt_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
1044 (*sqrt_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1045}

1047void ConvertSplitOperator(const Model& model,

1062 split_dim_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kInt32>().data;
1063 CHECK_EQ(split_dim_data.size(), 1);
1064 const int split_dim = split_dim_data[0];
1065 CreateDummyConcatDimTensorConst(src_op.inputs[0], split_dim,
1066 tensorflow_graph);
1067}

1243namespace {
1244// TODO(aselle): Remove when available in absl
1245absl::string_view FindLongestCommonPrefix(absl::string_view a,
1246 absl::string_view b) {
1247 if (a.empty() || b.empty()) return absl::string_view();
1248
1249 const char* pa = a.data();
1250 const char* pb = b.data();
1251 string::difference_type count = 0;
1252 const string::difference_type limit = std::min(a.size(), b.size());
1253 while (count < limit && *pa == *pb) {
1254 ++pa;
1255 ++pb;
1256 ++count;
1257 }
1258
1259 return absl::string_view(a.data(), count);
1260}

1262
1263void ConvertLstmCellOperator(const Model& model, const LstmCellOperator& src_op,
1264 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1265 // Find the base name
1266 const string base(
1267 FindLongestCommonPrefix(src_op.outputs[LstmCellOperator::STATE_OUTPUT],
1268 src_op.outputs[LstmCellOperator::ACTIV_OUTPUT]));
1269
1270 // Concatenate inputs
1271 const string concat_output = base + "basic_lstm_cell/concat";
1272 // Op names have been chosen to match the tf.slim LSTM naming
1273 // as closely as possible.
1274 const int axis =
1275 model.GetArray(src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::PREV_ACTIV_INPUT])
1276 .shape()
1277 .dimensions_count() -
1278 1;
1279 // Note that DATA_INPUT may have extra size 1 dimensions, but TF concat
1280 // works the same since the tensor has the same underlying data layout.
1281 const string axis_output = concat_output + "/axis";
1282 CreateDummyConcatDimTensorConst(axis_output, axis, tensorflow_graph);
1283 auto* concat_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1284 concat_op->set_op("ConcatV2");
1285 concat_op->set_name(concat_output);
1286 *concat_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::DATA_INPUT];
1287 *concat_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::PREV_ACTIV_INPUT];
1288 *concat_op->add_input() = axis_output;
1289 (*concat_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1290 (*concat_op->mutable_attr())["Tidx"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1291 (*concat_op->mutable_attr())["N"].set_i(2); // Number of inputs
1292
1293 // Write weights
1294 const string weights_output = base + "weights";
1295 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::WEIGHTS_INPUT]));
1296 const string weights_name = WalkUpToConstantArray(
1297 model, src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::WEIGHTS_INPUT]);
1298 const auto& weights_array = model.GetArray(weights_name);
1299 // Convert 4D FullyConnected weights into 2D matrix
1300 const auto& weights_shape = weights_array.shape();
1301 CHECK_EQ(weights_shape.dimensions_count(), 2);
1302 CHECK(weights_array.buffer);
1303 CHECK(weights_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
1304 const float* weights_data =
1305 weights_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
1306 ConvertFloatTensorConst(weights_output, weights_shape, weights_data,
1307 AxesOrder::kCR, AxesOrder::kRC, tensorflow_graph);
1308
1309 // Fully connected matrix multiply
1310 const string matmul_output = base + "MatMul";
1311 auto* matmul_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1312 matmul_op->set_op("MatMul");
1313 matmul_op->set_name(matmul_output);
1314 *matmul_op->add_input() = concat_output;
1315 *matmul_op->add_input() = weights_output;
1316 (*matmul_op->mutable_attr())["transpose_a"].set_b(false);
1317 (*matmul_op->mutable_attr())["transpose_b"].set_b(false);
1318 (*matmul_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1319
1320 // Write biases
1321 const string biases_output = base + "biases";
1322 CHECK(model.HasArray(src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::BIASES_INPUT]));
1323 const string bias_name = WalkUpToConstantArray(
1324 model, src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::BIASES_INPUT]);
1325 const auto& bias_array = model.GetArray(bias_name);
1326 // TODO(b/62904716) Bias arrays should be 1-D, and used directly.
1327 Shape bias_shape_1d = bias_array.shape();
1328 UnextendShape(&bias_shape_1d, 1);
1329 CHECK(bias_array.buffer);
1330 CHECK(bias_array.buffer->type == ArrayDataType::kFloat);
1331 const float* bias_data =
1332 bias_array.GetBuffer<ArrayDataType::kFloat>().data.data();
1333 ConvertFloatTensorConst(biases_output, bias_shape_1d, bias_data,
1334 AxesOrder::kOneAxis, AxesOrder::kOneAxis,
1335 tensorflow_graph,
1336 LegacyScalarPolicy::kDoCreateLegacyScalars);
1337
1338 // Add biases
1339 string biasadd_output = base + "BiasAdd";
1340 auto* biasadd_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1341 biasadd_op->set_op("BiasAdd");
1342 biasadd_op->set_name(biasadd_output);
1343 biasadd_op->add_input(matmul_output);
1344 biasadd_op->add_input(biases_output);
1345 (*biasadd_op->mutable_attr())["data_format"].set_s("NHWC");
1346 (*biasadd_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1347
1348 // Split
1349 string split_dim_output = base + "split/split_dim";
1350 // The dimension is the same as the concatenation dimension
1351 CreateDummyConcatDimTensorConst(split_dim_output, axis, tensorflow_graph);
1352 string split_output = base + "split";
1353 auto* split_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1354 split_op->set_op("Split");
1355 split_op->set_name(split_output);
1356 *split_op->add_input() = split_dim_output;
1357 *split_op->add_input() = biasadd_output;
1358 (*split_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1359 (*split_op->mutable_attr())["num_split"].set_i(4); // Split into four outputs
1360
1361 // Activation functions and memory computations
1362 const string tanh_0_output = base + "Tanh";
1363 auto* tanh_0_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1364 tanh_0_op->set_op("Tanh");
1365 tanh_0_op->set_name(tanh_0_output);
1366 *tanh_0_op->add_input() = split_output + ":1";
1367 (*tanh_0_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1368
1369 const string sigmoid_1_output = base + "Sigmoid_1";
1370 auto* logistic_1_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1371 logistic_1_op->set_op("Sigmoid");
1372 logistic_1_op->set_name(sigmoid_1_output);
1373 *logistic_1_op->add_input() = split_output;
1374 (*logistic_1_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1375
1376 const string mul_1_output = base + "mul_1";
1377 auto* mul_1_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1378 mul_1_op->set_op("Mul");
1379 mul_1_op->set_name(mul_1_output);
1380 *mul_1_op->add_input() = sigmoid_1_output;
1381 *mul_1_op->add_input() = tanh_0_output;
1382 (*mul_1_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1383
1384 const string sigmoid_0_output = base + "Sigmoid";
1385 auto* logistic_2_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1386 logistic_2_op->set_op("Sigmoid");
1387 logistic_2_op->set_name(sigmoid_0_output);
1388 *logistic_2_op->add_input() = split_output + ":2";
1389 (*logistic_2_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1390
1391 const string sigmoid_2_output = base + "Sigmoid_2";
1392 auto* logistic_3_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1393 logistic_3_op->set_op("Sigmoid");
1394 logistic_3_op->set_name(sigmoid_2_output);
1395 *logistic_3_op->add_input() = split_output + ":3";
1396 (*logistic_3_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1397
1398 const string mul_0_output = base + "mul";
1399 auto* mul_0_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1400 mul_0_op->set_op("Mul");
1401 mul_0_op->set_name(mul_0_output);
1402 *mul_0_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[LstmCellOperator::PREV_STATE_INPUT];
1403 *mul_0_op->add_input() = sigmoid_0_output;
1404 (*mul_0_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1405
1406 const string add_1_output = src_op.outputs[LstmCellOperator::STATE_OUTPUT];
1407 auto* add_1_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1408 add_1_op->set_op("Add");
1409 add_1_op->set_name(add_1_output);
1410 *add_1_op->add_input() = mul_0_output;
1411 *add_1_op->add_input() = mul_1_output;
1412 (*add_1_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1413
1414 const string tanh_1_output = base + "Tanh_1";
1415 auto* tanh_1_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1416 tanh_1_op->set_op("Tanh");
1417 tanh_1_op->set_name(tanh_1_output);
1418 *tanh_1_op->add_input() = add_1_output;
1419 (*tanh_1_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1420
1421 const string mul_2_output = src_op.outputs[LstmCellOperator::ACTIV_OUTPUT];
1422 auto* mul_2_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1423 mul_2_op->set_op("Mul");
1424 mul_2_op->set_name(mul_2_output);
1425 *mul_2_op->add_input() = tanh_1_output;
1426 *mul_2_op->add_input() = sigmoid_2_output;
1427 (*mul_2_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1428}

1462void ConvertPadOperator(const Model& model, const PadOperator& src_op,
1463 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1464 auto* new_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1465 new_op->set_op("Pad");
1466 new_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
1467 CHECK_EQ(src_op.inputs.size(), 2);
1468 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
1469 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
1470
1471 const auto params_type = GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
1472 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(params_type);
1473
1474 // Create the params tensor.
1475 auto* params_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1476 params_op->set_op("Const");
1477 params_op->set_name(src_op.inputs[1]);
1478 (*params_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1479 auto* tensor = (*params_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
1480 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
1481
1482 CHECK_EQ(src_op.left_padding.size(), src_op.right_padding.size());
1483 for (int i = 0; i < src_op.left_padding.size(); ++i) {
1484 tensor->add_int_val(src_op.left_padding[i]);
1485 tensor->add_int_val(src_op.right_padding[i]);
1486 }
1487 auto* shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
1488 shape->add_dim()->set_size(src_op.left_padding.size());
1489 shape->add_dim()->set_size(2);
1490}

1492void CreateSliceInput(const string& input_name, const std::vector<int>& values,
1493 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1494 auto* params_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1495 params_op->set_op("Const");
1496 params_op->set_name(input_name);
1497 (*params_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1498 auto* tensor = (*params_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
1499 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
1500
1501 for (int i = 0; i < values.size(); ++i) {
1502 tensor->add_int_val(values[i]);
1503 }
1504 auto* shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
1505 shape->add_dim()->set_size(values.size());
1506}

1508void ConvertStridedSliceOperator(const Model& model,
1509 const StridedSliceOperator& src_op,
1510 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1511 auto* new_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1512 new_op->set_op("StridedSlice");
1513 new_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
1514 CHECK_EQ(src_op.inputs.size(), 4);
1515 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
1516 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
1517 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[2];
1518 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[3];
1519
1520 const auto params_type = GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
1521 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(params_type);
1522
1523 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["Index"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1524 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["begin_mask"].set_i(src_op.begin_mask);
1525 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["ellipsis_mask"].set_i(src_op.ellipsis_mask);
1526 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["end_mask"].set_i(src_op.end_mask);
1527 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["new_axis_mask"].set_i(src_op.new_axis_mask);
1528 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["shrink_axis_mask"].set_i(src_op.shrink_axis_mask);
1529
1530 // Create tensors for start/stop indices and strides.
1531 CreateSliceInput(src_op.inputs[1], src_op.start_indices, tensorflow_graph);
1532 CreateSliceInput(src_op.inputs[2], src_op.stop_indices, tensorflow_graph);
1533 CreateSliceInput(src_op.inputs[3], src_op.strides, tensorflow_graph);
1534}
1535
1536void ConvertSliceOperator(const Model& model, const SliceOperator& src_op,
1537 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1538 auto* new_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1539 new_op->set_op("Slice");
1540 new_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
1541 CHECK_EQ(src_op.inputs.size(), 3);
1542 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
1543 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
1544 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[2];
1545
1546 const auto params_type = GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
1547 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(params_type);
1548 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["Index"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1549
1550 // Create tensors for begin and size inputs.
1551 CreateSliceInput(src_op.inputs[1], src_op.begin, tensorflow_graph);
1552 CreateSliceInput(src_op.inputs[2], src_op.size, tensorflow_graph);
1553}
1554
1555void ConvertMeanOperator(const Model& model, const MeanOperator& src_op,
1556 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1557 auto* new_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1558 new_op->set_op("Mean");
1559 new_op->set_name(src_op.outputs[0]);
1560 CHECK_EQ(src_op.inputs.size(), 2);
1561 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[0];
1562 *new_op->add_input() = src_op.inputs[1];
1563
1564 const auto params_type = GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
1565 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(params_type);
1566
1567 if (src_op.keep_dims) {
1568 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["keep_dims"].set_b(true);
1569 }
1570
1571 // Create the params tensor.
1572 auto* params_op = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1573 params_op->set_op("Const");
1574 params_op->set_name(src_op.inputs[1]);
1575 (*params_op->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1576 auto* tensor = (*params_op->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor();
1577 tensor->set_dtype(DT_INT32);
1578
1579 for (int i = 0; i < src_op.axis.size(); ++i) {
1580 tensor->add_int_val(src_op.axis[i]);
1581 }
1582 auto* shape = tensor->mutable_tensor_shape();
1583 shape->add_dim()->set_size(src_op.axis.size());
1584}

1586void ConvertSqueezeOperator(const Model& model, const SqueezeOperator& src_op,

1593
1594 const auto params_type = GetTensorFlowDataType(model, src_op.inputs[0]);
1595 (*new_op->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(params_type);
1596
1597 if (!src_op.squeeze_dims.empty()) {
1598 auto& squeeze_dims = (*new_op->mutable_attr())["squeeze_dims"];
1599 for (int i : src_op.squeeze_dims) {
1600 squeeze_dims.mutable_list()->add_i(i);
1601 }
1602 }
1603}

1671void ConvertOperator(const Model& model, const Operator& src_op,
1672 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1673 if (src_op.fused_activation_function != FusedActivationFunctionType::kNone) {
1674 LOG(FATAL)
1675 << "Unsupported: the input model has a fused activation function";
1676 }
1677
1678 if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kConv) {
1679 ConvertConvOperator(model, static_cast<const ConvOperator&>(src_op),
1680 tensorflow_graph);
1681 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kDepthwiseConv) {
1682 ConvertDepthwiseConvOperator(
1683 model, static_cast<const DepthwiseConvOperator&>(src_op),
1684 tensorflow_graph);
1685 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kDepthToSpace) {
1686 ConvertDepthToSpaceOperator(
1687 model, static_cast<const DepthToSpaceOperator&>(src_op),
1688 tensorflow_graph);
1689 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kSpaceToDepth) {
1690 ConvertSpaceToDepthOperator(
1691 model, static_cast<const SpaceToDepthOperator&>(src_op),
1692 tensorflow_graph);
1693 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kFullyConnected) {
1694 ConvertFullyConnectedOperator(
1695 model, static_cast<const FullyConnectedOperator&>(src_op),
1696 tensorflow_graph);
1697 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kAdd) {
1698 ConvertAddOperator(model, static_cast<const AddOperator&>(src_op),
1699 tensorflow_graph);
1700 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kAddN) {
1701 ConvertAddNOperator(model, static_cast<const AddNOperator&>(src_op),
1702 tensorflow_graph);
1703 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kMul) {
1704 ConvertMulOperator(model, static_cast<const MulOperator&>(src_op),
1705 tensorflow_graph);
1706 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kRelu) {
1707 ConvertReluOperator(static_cast<const ReluOperator&>(src_op),
1708 tensorflow_graph);
1709 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kRelu1) {
1710 ConvertRelu1Operator(static_cast<const Relu1Operator&>(src_op),
1711 tensorflow_graph);
1712 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kRelu6) {
1713 ConvertRelu6Operator(static_cast<const Relu6Operator&>(src_op),
1714 tensorflow_graph);
1715 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kLog) {
1716 ConvertLogOperator(static_cast<const LogOperator&>(src_op),
1717 tensorflow_graph);
1718 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kLogistic) {
1719 ConvertLogisticOperator(static_cast<const LogisticOperator&>(src_op),
1720 tensorflow_graph);
1721 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTanh) {
1722 ConvertTanhOperator(static_cast<const TanhOperator&>(src_op),
1723 tensorflow_graph);
1724 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kL2Normalization) {
1725 ConvertL2NormalizationOperator(
1726 static_cast<const L2NormalizationOperator&>(src_op), tensorflow_graph);
1727 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kSoftmax) {
1728 ConvertSoftmaxOperator(model, static_cast<const SoftmaxOperator&>(src_op),
1729 tensorflow_graph);
1730 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kLogSoftmax) {
1731 ConvertLogSoftmaxOperator(model,
1732 static_cast<const LogSoftmaxOperator&>(src_op),
1733 tensorflow_graph);
1734 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kLocalResponseNormalization) {
1735 ConvertLocalResponseNormalizationOperator(
1736 static_cast<const LocalResponseNormalizationOperator&>(src_op),
1737 tensorflow_graph);
1738 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kLstmCell) {
1739 ConvertLstmCellOperator(model, static_cast<const LstmCellOperator&>(src_op),
1740 tensorflow_graph);
1741 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kMaxPool) {
1742 ConvertMaxPoolOperator(static_cast<const MaxPoolOperator&>(src_op),
1743 tensorflow_graph);
1744 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kAveragePool) {
1745 ConvertAveragePoolOperator(static_cast<const AveragePoolOperator&>(src_op),
1746 tensorflow_graph);
1747 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kConcatenation) {
1748 ConvertConcatenationOperator(
1749 model, static_cast<const ConcatenationOperator&>(src_op),
1750 tensorflow_graph);
1751 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowReshape) {
1752 ConvertTensorFlowReshapeOperator(
1753 model, static_cast<const TensorFlowReshapeOperator&>(src_op),
1754 tensorflow_graph);
1755 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kL2Pool) {
1756 ConvertL2PoolOperator(static_cast<const L2PoolOperator&>(src_op),
1757 tensorflow_graph);
1758 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowSquare) {
1759 ConvertSquareOperator(static_cast<const TensorFlowSquareOperator&>(src_op),
1760 tensorflow_graph);
1761 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowSqrt) {
1762 ConvertSqrtOperator(static_cast<const TensorFlowSqrtOperator&>(src_op),
1763 tensorflow_graph);
1764 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowSplit) {
1765 ConvertSplitOperator(model,
1766 static_cast<const TensorFlowSplitOperator&>(src_op),
1767 tensorflow_graph);
1768 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kFakeQuant) {
1769 ConvertFakeQuantOperator(static_cast<const FakeQuantOperator&>(src_op),
1770 tensorflow_graph);
1771 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kCast) {
1772 ConvertCastOperator(model, static_cast<const CastOperator&>(src_op),
1773 tensorflow_graph);
1774 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kFloor) {
1775 ConvertFloorOperator(model, static_cast<const FloorOperator&>(src_op),
1776 tensorflow_graph);
1777 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kGather) {
1778 ConvertGatherOperator(model, static_cast<const GatherOperator&>(src_op),
1779 tensorflow_graph);
1780 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kResizeBilinear) {
1781 ConvertResizeBilinearOperator(
1782 model, static_cast<const ResizeBilinearOperator&>(src_op),
1783 tensorflow_graph);
1784 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kSpaceToBatchND) {
1785 ConvertSpaceToBatchNDOperator(
1786 model, static_cast<const SpaceToBatchNDOperator&>(src_op),
1787 tensorflow_graph);
1788 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kBatchToSpaceND) {
1789 ConvertBatchToSpaceNDOperator(
1790 model, static_cast<const BatchToSpaceNDOperator&>(src_op),
1791 tensorflow_graph);
1792 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kPad) {
1793 ConvertPadOperator(model, static_cast<const PadOperator&>(src_op),
1794 tensorflow_graph);
1795 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kStridedSlice) {
1796 ConvertStridedSliceOperator(
1797 model, static_cast<const StridedSliceOperator&>(src_op),
1798 tensorflow_graph);
1799 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kMean) {
1800 ConvertMeanOperator(model, static_cast<const MeanOperator&>(src_op),
1801 tensorflow_graph);
1802 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kSub) {
1803 ConvertSubOperator(model, static_cast<const SubOperator&>(src_op),
1804 tensorflow_graph);
1805 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowMinimum) {
1806 ConvertTensorFlowMinimumOperator(
1807 model, static_cast<const TensorFlowMinimumOperator&>(src_op),
1808 tensorflow_graph);
1809 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowMaximum) {
1810 ConvertTensorFlowMaximumOperator(
1811 model, static_cast<const TensorFlowMaximumOperator&>(src_op),
1812 tensorflow_graph);
1813 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kSqueeze) {
1814 ConvertSqueezeOperator(model, static_cast<const SqueezeOperator&>(src_op),
1815 tensorflow_graph);
1816 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kSlice) {
1817 ConvertSliceOperator(model, static_cast<const SliceOperator&>(src_op),
1818 tensorflow_graph);
1819 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kArgMax) {
1820 ConvertArgMaxOperator(model, static_cast<const ArgMaxOperator&>(src_op),
1821 tensorflow_graph);
1822 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTopK_V2) {
1823 ConvertTopKV2Operator(model, static_cast<const TopKV2Operator&>(src_op),
1824 tensorflow_graph);
1825 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTranspose) {
1826 ConvertTransposeOperator(
1827 model, static_cast<const TransposeOperator&>(src_op), tensorflow_graph);
1828 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTensorFlowShape) {
1829 ConvertTensorFlowShapeOperator(
1830 model, static_cast<const TensorFlowShapeOperator&>(src_op),
1831 tensorflow_graph);
1832 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kRank) {
1833 ConvertRankOperator(model, static_cast<const RankOperator&>(src_op),
1834 tensorflow_graph);
1835 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kRange) {
1836 ConvertRangeOperator(model, static_cast<const RangeOperator&>(src_op),
1837 tensorflow_graph);
1838 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kStack) {
1839 ConvertStackOperator(model, static_cast<const StackOperator&>(src_op),
1840 tensorflow_graph);
1841 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kFill) {
1842 ConvertFillOperator(model, static_cast<const FillOperator&>(src_op),
1843 tensorflow_graph);
1844 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kFloorDiv) {
1845 ConvertFloorDivOperator(model, static_cast<const FloorDivOperator&>(src_op),
1846 tensorflow_graph);
1847 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kExpandDims) {
1848 ConvertExpandDimsOperator(model,
1849 static_cast<const ExpandDimsOperator&>(src_op),
1850 tensorflow_graph);
1851 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kTransposeConv) {
1852 ConvertTransposeConvOperator(
1853 model, static_cast<const TransposeConvOperator&>(src_op),
1854 tensorflow_graph);
1855 } else if (src_op.type == OperatorType::kRandomUniform) {
1856 ConvertRandomUniformOperator(
1857 model, static_cast<const RandomUniformOperator&>(src_op),
1858 tensorflow_graph);
1859 } else {
1860 LOG(FATAL) << "Unhandled operator type " << OperatorTypeName(src_op.type);
1861 }
1862}
1863
1864void AddPlaceholder(const string& name, ArrayDataType type,
1865 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1866 auto* placeholder = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1867 placeholder->set_op("Placeholder");
1868 switch (type) {
1869 case ArrayDataType::kBool:
1870 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_BOOL);
1871 break;
1872 case ArrayDataType::kFloat:
1873 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1874 break;
1875 case ArrayDataType::kUint8:
1876 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_UINT8);
1877 break;
1878 case ArrayDataType::kInt32:
1879 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1880 break;
1881 case ArrayDataType::kInt64:
1882 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT64);
1883 break;
1884 case ArrayDataType::kInt16:
1885 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT16);
1886 break;
1887 default:
1888 LOG(FATAL) << "Unexpected data type in array \"" << name << "\"";
1889 }
1890 placeholder->set_name(name);
1891}
1892
1893void AddPlaceholderForRNNState(const Model& model, const string& name, int size,
1894 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1895 auto* placeholder = tensorflow_graph->add_node();
1896 placeholder->set_op("Placeholder");
1897 placeholder->set_name(name);
1898 (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1899
1900 auto* shape = (*placeholder->mutable_attr())["shape"].mutable_shape();
1901 const auto& state_array = model.GetArray(name);
1902 if (state_array.has_shape()) {
1903 const auto& state_shape = state_array.shape();
1904 const int kDims = state_shape.dimensions_count();
1905 for (int i = 0; i < kDims; ++i) {
1906 shape->add_dim()->set_size(state_shape.dims(i));
1907 }
1908 } else {
1909 shape->add_dim()->set_size(1);
1910 shape->add_dim()->set_size(size);
1911 }
1912}
1913
1914void ExportTensorFlowGraphDefImplementation(const Model& model,
1915 GraphDef* tensorflow_graph) {
1916 for (const auto& input_array : model.flags.input_arrays()) {
1917 AddPlaceholder(input_array.name(),
1918 model.GetArray(input_array.name()).data_type,
1919 tensorflow_graph);
1920 }
1921 for (const auto& rnn_state : model.flags.rnn_states()) {
1922 AddPlaceholderForRNNState(model, rnn_state.state_array(), rnn_state.size(),
1923 tensorflow_graph);
1924 }
1925 for (const auto& op : model.operators) {
1926 ConvertOperator(model, *op, tensorflow_graph);
1927 }
1928 // Generically export arrays that haven't been exported already
1929 // by the above operators export. It's important that this comes
1930 // after, as some operators need to export arrays that they reference
1931 // in a specific way, rather than in the generic way done below.
1932 for (const auto& array_pair : model.GetArrayMap()) {
1933 const string& array_name = array_pair.first;
1934 const auto& array = *array_pair.second;
1935 if (array.buffer) {
1936 switch (array.data_type) {
1937 case ArrayDataType::kFloat:
1938 ConvertFloatTensorConst(model, array_name, tensorflow_graph);
1939 break;
1940 case ArrayDataType::kInt32:
1941 ConvertIntTensorConst(model, array_name, tensorflow_graph);
1942 break;
1943 default:
1944 break;
1945 }
1946 }
1947 }
1948}
1949} // namespace
1950
1951void EncodeConstantArraysMinMaxByWrappingThemInFakeQuantNodes(Model* model) {
1952 for (const auto& array_kv : model->GetArrayMap()) {
1953 const string& array_name = array_kv.first;
1954 Array& array = *array_kv.second;
1955 if (!array.buffer || !array.minmax) {
1956 continue;
1957 }
1958 const string& wrapped_array_name =
1959 AvailableArrayName(*model, array_name + "/data");
1960 Array& wrapped_array = model->GetOrCreateArray(wrapped_array_name);
1961 wrapped_array.data_type = array.data_type;
1962 wrapped_array.copy_shape(array.shape());
1963 wrapped_array.buffer = std::move(array.buffer);
1964 FakeQuantOperator* fakequant_op = new FakeQuantOperator;
1965 fakequant_op->inputs = {wrapped_array_name};
1966 fakequant_op->outputs = {array_name};
1967 fakequant_op->minmax.reset(new MinMax);
1968 *fakequant_op->minmax = *array.minmax;
1969 const auto& it = FindOpWithInput(*model, array_name);
1970 model->operators.emplace(it, fakequant_op);
1971 }
1972 CheckInvariants(*model);
1973}
1974
1975void ExportTensorFlowGraphDef(const Model& model,
1976 string* output_file_contents) {
1977 CHECK(output_file_contents->empty());
1978 GraphDef tensorflow_graph;
1979 ExportTensorFlowGraphDefImplementation(model, &tensorflow_graph);
1980 LogDumpGraphDef(kLogLevelModelChanged, "AT EXPORT", tensorflow_graph);
1981 CHECK(tensorflow_graph.SerializeToString(output_file_contents));
1982}
